
[1]behoof

   BEHOOF', n.

   1. Radically, need, necessity; whence, by an easy analogy, the word
   came to signify that which supplies want. Hence, in present usage.

   2. That which is advantageous; advantage; profit; benefit.

   No mean recompense it brings to your behoof.
